Zinedine Zidane has called for Thierry Henry to bid a final farewell to the France national team by playing in their friendly against Brazil in March.

Henry is now out of contract with MLS side New York Red Bulls, but claims he is yet to make a decision about his future.

Despite retiring from international football in 2010, French newspaper L'Equipe have started a campaign to get the striker back is Les Bleus for a final time next year.

