The Brazil friendly is due to take place at the Stade de France on March 26, which could mean Henry having to keep his fitness up between now and next year.

The 37-year-old is already being linked to a move back to Arsenal and Gunners boss Arsene Wenger believes the Emirates icon will return in the future.

Wenger said: 'Certainly one day he will come back here. In what role I don’t know, that is what he has to think about: what direction he wants to give to his next life.'

